cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sequence labeling to solve arithmetic word problems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a novel approach to automatically discovering hidden mathematical relations in word problems.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the approach involves training a model to tag quantities with mathematical signs.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is possible as the paper mentions the use of neural networks in the approach.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of visual information in some of the datasets used for evaluation.
